#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:5
msgid "Making a release"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:7
msgid ""
"For branch organization we use a variation of the [GitHub Flow](https://"
"guides.github.com/introduction/flow/) with the latest release branch named "
"`stable` (due to ReadTheDocs constraints)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:11
msgid "Making a major release"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:13
msgid "Assume for concreteness that we are releasing version 0.20.0."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:15
#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:87
#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:164
msgid "Preparation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:17
msgid ""
"Make a tracking issue with a title like \"0.20.0 release planning\". Add the "
"checklist:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:19
msgid "[ ] Update packages"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:20
msgid "[ ] Look for open PRs to add to the release milestone"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:21
msgid "[ ] Make sure all PRs in the release milestone are merged"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:22
msgid "[ ] Write release notes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:23
msgid "[ ] Tidy changelog"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:25
msgid ""
"Make a release notes blog post at pyodide-blog: https://github.com/pyodide/"
"pyodide-blog"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:28
msgid ""
"Generate the list of contributors for the release at the end of the release "
"notes blog post with:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:31
msgid ""
"git shortlog -s 0.19.0.. | cut -f2- | grep -v '\\[bot\\]' | sort --ignore-"
"case | tr '\\n' ';' | sed 's/;/, /g;s/, $//' | fold -s\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:35
msgid "where `0.19.0` is the tag for the last major release."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:37
msgid ""
"Read the changelog and tidy it up by adding subsections, organizing, and "
"proof reading it. Make a pull request with these changes titled \"Rearrange "
"changelog for 0.20.0 release\" and merge it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:41
msgid ""
"Make sure all the PRs that we want to release are merged and that the "
"release notes are ready."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:43
#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:145
msgid "Releasing"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:45
msgid "Switch to the main branch"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:46
msgid ""
"Replace the `## Unreleased` heading in the changelog with `## Version "
"0.20.0` and add the date underneath it. Commit this."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:48
#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:148
#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:176
msgid "From the root of the repository run:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:49
msgid "./tools/bump_version.py 0.20.0 --tag\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:52
#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:152
#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:180
msgid "This makes a release commit and tags it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:53
msgid ""
"Push the release commit and tag to upstream. This triggers the release CI."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:54
msgid "git push upstream main 0.20.0\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:57
msgid "Wait for CI to pass and release to be created."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:58
msgid ""
"Rename the `stable` branch to a release branch for the previous major "
"version. For instance if last release was, `0.20.0`, the corresponding "
"release branch would be `0.20.X`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:62
msgid ""
"git fetch upstream stable:stable\n"
"git branch 0.20.X stable\n"
"git push -u upstream 0.20.X\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:68
msgid "Create a new `stable` branch:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:70
msgid ""
"git switch main\n"
"git switch -C stable\n"
"git push upstream stable --force\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:76
msgid "Set the version back to next development version with:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:77
msgid ""
"git switch main\n"
"./tools/bump_version.py 0.21.0 --dev\n"
"git push upstream main\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:83
msgid "Making a minor release"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:85
msgid "Assume for concreteness that we are releasing version 0.27.2."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:89
msgid ""
"Go through the commits on the main branch since the last release, find ones "
"you want to backport and add the \"needs backport\" label to the pull "
"requests. You can do this manually in the web interface on the GitHub PR or "
"you can use"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:93
msgid "./tools/backports.py add-pr <pr-number>\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:97
msgid ""
"List out the `needs backport` PRs that are missing changelog entries with"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:99
msgid "./tools/backports.py missing-changelogs\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:103
msgid ""
"and double check that every PR that should have a changelog does have one."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:105
msgid ""
"Read the changelog and tidy it up by adding subsections, organizing, and "
"proof reading it. Make a pull request with these changes titled e.g., "
"\"Rearrange changelog for 0.27.2 release\" and merge it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:109
msgid "Make the backport branch (on top of stable):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:111
msgid "./tools/backports.py backport-branch\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:115
msgid "Make the update-changelog branch (on top of main) with:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:117
msgid "./tools/backports.py changelog-branch\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:121
msgid "Open PRs for these two branches with:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:123
msgid "./tools/backports.py open-release-prs\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:127
msgid "Use the backport branch PR as the release tracker."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:129
msgid ""
"Make sure that the CI passes on the backports branch and it is approved. "
"When it does pass, set the date for the release in the changelog with:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:131
msgid ""
"./tools/backports.py set-date\n"
"git switch backports-for-0.27.2\n"
"git push -f\n"
"git switch changelog-for-0.27.2\n"
"git push -f\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:138
msgid "Then merge the two PRs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:139
msgid "Run"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:140
msgid "./tools/backport.py clear-prs\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:143
msgid "to clear all the \"needs backport\" labels."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:147
msgid "Switch to the stable branch and `git pull`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:149
msgid "./tools/backport.py bump-version --tag\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:153
msgid ""
"Push the release commit and tag to `upstream/stable`. This triggers the "
"release CI."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:155
msgid "git push upstream stable 0.27.2\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:158
#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:191
msgid "Wait for CI to pass and the release to be created."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:160
msgid "Making an alpha release"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:162
msgid "Assume for concreteness that we are releasing 0.28.0a1."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:166
msgid ""
"Any single maintainer can decide on their own to make an alpha release, it "
"is not required to discuss it with other maintainers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:169
msgid ""
"Name the first alpha release `x.x.xa1` and in subsequent alphas increment "
"the final number. No preparation is necessary. Do not make any changes to "
"the changelog."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:173
msgid "Release instructions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:175
msgid "Switch to the main branch and `git pull`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:177
msgid "./tools/bump_version.py 0.28.0a1 --tag\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:181
msgid ""
"Push the release commit and tag to `upstream/main`. This triggers the "
"release CI."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:183
msgid "git push upstream main 0.28.0a1\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:186
msgid "Put the version back with:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:187
msgid ""
"git revert 0.28.0a1 -n && git commit -m \"Back to development version\"\n"
"git push upstream main\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:193
msgid "Fixing documentation for a released version"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:195
msgid ""
"Cherry pick the corresponding documentation commits to the `stable` branch. "
"Use `git commit --amend` to add `[skip ci]` to the commit message."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:198
msgid "Updating the Docker image"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:200
msgid ""
"Anyone with an account on hub.docker.com can follow the following steps:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:202
msgid "Make whatever changes are needed to the Dockerfile."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:203
msgid ""
"Build the docker image with `docker build .` in the Pyodide root directory. "
"If the build succeeds, docker will give you a hash for the built image."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:205
msgid ""
"Use `python ./tools/docker_image_tag.py` to find out what the new image tag "
"should be. Tag the image with:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:207
msgid ""
"docker image tag <image-hash> <your-docker-username>/pyodide-env:<image-"
"tag>\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:210
msgid "Push the image with:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:211
msgid "docker image push <your-docker-username>/pyodide-env:<image-tag>\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:214
msgid ""
"Replace the image in `.circleci/config.yml` with your newly created image. "
"Open a pull request with your changes to `Dockerfile` and `.circleci/config."
"yml`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:216
msgid ""
"When the tests pass and the pull request is approved, a maintainer must copy "
"the new image into the `pyodide` dockerhub account."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:218
msgid ""
"Then replace the image tag in `.circleci/config.yml`, `.devcontainer/"
"devcontainer.json`, and `run_docker` with the new image under the `pyodide` "
"dockerhub account."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:222
msgid ""
"It's also possible to update the docker image by pushing your changes to the "
"`Dockerfile` to a branch in the `pyodide/pyodide` repo (not on a fork) and "
"clicking `Run workflow` on https://github.com/pyodide/pyodide/actions/"
"workflows/docker_image.yml."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:229
msgid "Updating packages"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:231
msgid ""
"Before updating the Python version and before making a major Pyodide "
"release, we try to update all packages that are not too much trouble. Run"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:234
msgid "make -C packages update-all\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:238
msgid ""
"to update all packages and make a pull request with these changes. There "
"will be build/test failures, revert the packages that fail the build or "
"tests and make a note to update them independently."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:242
msgid "Updating pyodide-build"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:244
msgid ""
"To change the version of pyodide-build, change the commit of the pyodide-"
"build submodule."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:246
msgid ""
"cd pyodide-build\n"
"git checkout \"<COMMIT HASH>\"\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:251
msgid ""
"To test with a fork of pyodide-build, change the `.gitmodules` file to point "
"to your fork and update the commit hash"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:253
msgid ""
"# .gitmodules\n"
"[submodule \"pyodide-build\"]\n"
"\tpath = pyodide-build\n"
"\turl = https://github.com/<yourfork>/pyodide-build\n"
