#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:260
msgid ""
"git submodule sync\n"
"cd pyodide-build\n"
"git checkout \"<COMMIT HASH>\"\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:266
msgid "Upgrading the ABI"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:268
msgid ""
"Each year, we aim to release a new Pyodide ABI version with a new CPython "
"and Emscripten version."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:271
msgid ""
"Similar to the CPython alpha release, we stabilize the ABI early before "
"releasing the new Pyodide version so that package maintainers can update "
"their packages to use the new ABI ([#5580](https://github.com/pyodide/"
"pyodide/issues/5580))."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:275
msgid "0. Stabilize and freeze the ABI"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:277
msgid ""
"Discuss with the maintainers to decide what ABI changes to make before the "
"release."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:280
msgid ""
"Once the ABI changes are decided, create a `20XX_0` branch (targeting year) "
"from the `main` branch. All PRs that change the ABI should be merged to the "
"`20XX_0` branch."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:284
msgid "1. Disable `USE_PREBUILT_PACKAGES`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:286
msgid ""
"Pyodide CI uses prebuilt packages built with the ABI of the last release. To "
"upgrade the ABI, you need to disable them, otherwise the CI will fail."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:289
msgid ""
"Find the `USE_PREBUILT_PACKAGES` environment variable in [.circleci/config."
"yml](https://github.com/ryanking13/pyodide/blob/unvendor-recipes/.circleci/"
"config.yml) and set it to `false`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:293
msgid "2. Upgrade Emscripten and CPython version"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:295
msgid "Update the Emscripten and CPython versions respectively."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:297
msgid ""
"Updating the Emscripten version is not mandatory, but it is recommended to "
"benefit from the latest features and bug fixes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:300
msgid ""
"Updating Emscripten and CPython separately is often easier than updating "
"them together."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:303
msgid "2.1. Upgrade the Emscripten version"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:305
msgid "Updating Emscripten requires the following three steps:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:307
msgid "Rebase the patches in `emsdk/patches` onto the new Emscripten version."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:308
msgid "Update the Emscripten version in `Makefile.envs`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:309
msgid ""
"Update the `struct_info` JSON file in `src/js/` to match the version of the "
"file in Emscripten."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:312
msgid ""
"All three steps are automated by `tools/update_emscripten.py`. To update, "
"run:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:314
msgid "./tools/update_emscripten.py new_version\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:318
msgid ""
"If there are rebase conflicts, you will have to manually finish the rebase. "
"Once the rebase is completed, rerun `update_emscripten.py`. It will start "
"over the rebase from scratch but reuse your conflict resolutions using the "
"git rerere feature."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:323
msgid ""
"After this is done, commit all the changes and open a PR. There are "
"frequently complicated CI failures."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:326
msgid "2.2. Upgrade CPython version"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:328
msgid "Prerequisites"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:330
msgid "The desired version of CPython must be available at:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:332
msgid "The \"specific release\" section of https://www.python.org/downloads"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:333
msgid "https://hub.docker.com/_/python"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:334
msgid "https://github.com/actions/python-versions/releases"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:336
msgid "Steps"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:338
msgid ""
"Follow the steps in \"Updating the Docker image\" to create a Docker image "
"for the new Python version."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:341
msgid ""
"Make sure you are in a Python virtual environment with the new version of "
"Python and with `requirements.txt` installed. (It is also possible to work "
"in the Docker image as an alternative.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:345
msgid "Update the Python version in `Makefile.envs`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:347
msgid "Update the Python version in the following locations:"
