msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:452
msgid ""
"Most likely, some packages will fail to build. You can disable them by "
"adding `_disabled: true` to the recipes of the failing packages. You don't "
"need to handle all the build failures in the same PR—you can open multiple "
"PRs to fix the build failures or let the package maintainers handle them."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:457
msgid ""
"Create a new tag for the new package set when the build is successful. This "
"will create a new release with the new package set."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:460
msgid ""
"5. Re-enable `USE_PREBUILT_PACKAGES` and upgrade the ABI in the main branch"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:462
msgid ""
"Go back to `pyodide/pyodide` and update the `PYODIDE_PREBUILT_PACKAGES_BASE` "
"variable in `Makefile.envs` to the new package set you created in the "
"previous step."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:466
msgid ""
"Then re-enable `USE_PREBUILT_PACKAGES` in `.circleci/config.yml` and open a "
"PR to merge it into the main branch."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:469
msgid "6. Release a new Pyodide version"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:471
msgid ""
"After enabling most of the packages that were available in the previous ABI "
"version, we are ready to release a new Pyodide version with the new ABI."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:474
msgid "Update {ref}`pyodide-platform-abi` to match the new ABI."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../development/maintainers.md:476
msgid ""
"Merge the `20XX_0` branch into `main` and open a PR, then release a new "
"Pyodide version with the new ABI."
msgstr ""
